description: A thoroughbred horse named First Receiver which was owned by the late Queen and bred at her Sandringham stud is in line for a Horse of the Year prize - one of equestrian's most prestigious titles.

title: MAIL ON SUNDAY COMMENT: An admirable show of restraint in the face of Labour's bigotry
description: MAIL ON SUNDAY COMMENT: Chancellor Kwasi Kwarteng, in his interview today with The Mail on Sunday, is cool and thoughtful about the storm which engulfed him.

title: Parents brace for return of 'boomerang kids' with one FIFTH of 18-34 year-olds consider moving home
description: A fifth of supposedly independent adults aged 18 to 34 say are considering moving back in with their paretns to avoid rising rent, energy and food bills.

title: Tributes to Mail on Sunday's Scott Gormley, 78, who 'helped make Financial Mail best of its kind'
description: Scott Gormley (pictured), a senior production journalist on The Mail on Sunday for many years, has died aged 78 after a long illness. Scott began his career on local newspapers in Shropshire.

title: A burger might cheer you up: Beef is only food linked to a lower risk of depression, study reveals
description: If the thought of a salad makes you glum, tucking into a burger is best for cheering you up, say scientists. Beef was the only food linked to a lower risk of depression in a study on 440,000 Brits.

title: Kwasi Kwarteng's mini-budget could cost £25billion - almost half of the Government forecast
description: Analysis by the Centre for Economics and Business Research suggests Kwasi Kwarteng's mini Budget will add £25billion to the country's deficit - far less  than his critics suggest.

title: Frank Skinner has recorded new World Cup version of Three Lions paying tribute to the Lionesses
description: With England gearing up for yet another tilt at ending all those years of hurt, Skinner is dusting off the old classic with long-time collaborator, Ian Broudie of the Lightning Seeds.

title: Mastermind behind King Charles's coronation bestowed with a 'quick' knighthood
description: King Charles III gave an accolade to the 18th Duke of Norfolk, the most senior peer in Britain, just 10 days after inheriting the throne from his mother.

title: Rebekah Vardy avoids new court clash by agreeing to fight over the 'Wagatha Christie' in writing
description: Mrs Vardy say that she is relieved she will not have to set foot in the High Court again after her defeat to Mrs Rooney in the 'Wagatha Christie' in the libel case.

title: Tesco ties top executive bonuses to slashing food waste by half
description: The move by the UK's biggest supermarket is a boost for The Mail on Sunday's War On Food Waste campaign and will also put pressure on rivals to be more ambitious.

title: Kerry Katona says ex-husband George Kay would beat her EVERY DAY
description: The TV personality, 42, has revealed that her late ex-husband George Kay would beat her every day during their relationship - even attempting to strangle her while driving.

title: Co-op rolls out thinner glass on wine bottles to reduce its carbon footprint
description: With those wines alone, the Co-op will save 1,000 tons of carbon across the 850,000 bottles sold each year - the equivalent of taking 215 cars off the road.

title: Money laundering! Britons lose £800m in washing machines every YEAR new study claims
description: It might not qualify as money laundering in the morally questionable sense - but a new study claims that Britons may be losing an astonishing £800m a year in washing machines and dryers.

title: Bargain hunting shoppers hit by multi-buy 'deal-flation' with offer prices rising by 20 per cent
description: Shoppers are warned to watch out for 'deal-flation' as stores hike food offer prices by 20 per cent. M&S, Morrisons, Tesco and Waitrose bumped up cost of deals by up to double the inflation rate.

title: Lawyer who threw Molotov cocktail at NYPD car during George Floyd protests says she was drunk
description: Urooj Rahman, 33, along with Colinford Mattis, 35,  pleaded guilty to conspiracy charges punishable by no more than five years imprisonment in June over the destruction.

title: Merriwa crash kills 10-year-old boy and hospitalises 15-year-old girl
description: The vehicle veered off the road and hit a tree before it rolled several times on Flaggs Road at Merriwa, in the Hunter region of NSW, at 11am on Saturday.

title: Want to save £700 a year? Turn the heat down 1C, switch to LEDs and unplug your chargers
description: The exact amount you will have to pay will depend on how much energy you use. But as winter sets in, millions of consumers will face the choice between cutting back on energy or falling into fuel poverty.

title: Eco-zealots who call UK 'genocidal' launch hysteria protests marking start of an 'October uprising'
description: Members of the group Just Stop Oil occupied four bridges in the capital, causing gridlock on busy roads, before converging on Parliament.

title: Mystery behind Meghan Markle's 'bloodsoaked' earrings from Saudi prince is unravelled by new book
description: During a royal tour of Fiji, Meghan wore an eye-catching pair of diamond earrings. It was later revealed they were a gift from Saudi prince Mohammed bin Salman.

title: Actors charity 'let down' On The Buses star Anna Karen, 85, who was killed in a house fire
description: A prestigious actors' charity has been accused of 'failing' On The Buses star Anna Karen after she died in a fire in February this year. Bedbound Ms Karen, 85, was killed at her East London home.

title: Treasury defends Kwasi Kwarteng joining event hosted by hedge fund boss
description: The Treasury has defended Kwasi Kwarteng's decision to attend an event hosted by a hedge fund boss as traders drove down the value of the pound.

title: Huge 215ft tall steelworks is blown up using 1.6 tonnes of explosives in the UK's biggest demolition
description: According to the Tees Valley Combined Authority, the demolition, which used around 1.6 tonnes of explosives, is one of the largest of its kind ever to take place in the UK.

title: Student, 21, who took his life in lockdown was one of eleven in just six years at Exeter University
description: At least 11 students at Exeter University have taken their own lives in the past six years, The Mail on Sunday can reveal. The parents of one will say this week that staff did not do enough to help their son.

title: Labour Left angry as Keir Starmer brings back key Blairites, including ex-PM's speech writer
description: A senior left-wing MP said: 'Starmer (pictured) stood on a Left-wing, Corbyn continuity platform but he's ripping all that up to allow a New Labour makeover of the party.'

title: Qatari sheik accuses top art dealer of duping him with £4.5m forgeries
description: Sheik Hamad bin Abdullah al-Thani says John Eskenazi passed off modern fakes as historic works of art - including a piece he claims contained bits of plastic - and is suing him for a refund.

title: A heart-rending dispatch from the moors as new police hunt for Keith Bennett enters third day
description: Winnie Johnson went to her grave a decade ago never surrendering hope that her son Keith Bennett would be found. How many times did that poor woman skirt the spot now marked by two blue tents?

title: Nick Clegg makes £3.6m profit on his luxury five-bedroom Silicon Valley mansion
description: Nick Clegg, now president of global affairs and communications for Meta, as Facebook has been rebranded, sold the house in Atherton, America's wealthiest town, four days ago for £10.3 million.

title: Jeremy Corbyn 'to lose his Islington North seat to former MP'
description: Jeremy Corbyn is likely to lose his Islington North seat to a Labour MP who blamed his leadership for her defeat at the last election. Corbyn is said to be planning to stand as an independent.
